data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>()` (MSTest v3+). It asserts the type *and* returns the typed instance, eliminating the manual cast:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

This gives you a clearer failure message (e.g., "Expected type EmailHandler, actual type SmsHandler") instead of an opaque `InvalidCastException`.
